  <chapter xml:id="careers" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
      <title>Careers in Mathematics</title>
        <p>What kind of job can I get after college? We hear the question repeatedly from students and parents.
        It's a valid question, and one worth some time to think about. Truthfully, the value of an understanding
        of mathematics is becoming increasingly recognized.</p>

        <p>
          It's not just about calculation. Mathematics teaches us how to think critically, to problem solve, and
          to not get caught trying to solve every problem with the same approach. There is an underestimated amount
          of creativity involved in doing mathematics well, and these skills make math students quick learners and
          valuable employees.
        </p>

